nodes.bodyText:
CharFilter should be abstract layer. I don't think service can accept the user-defined charFilter as there is odata.type defined here.
@JsonSubTypes({
    @JsonSubTypes.Type(name = "#Microsoft.Azure.Search.MappingCharFilter", value = MappingCharFilter.class),
    @JsonSubTypes.Type(name = "#Microsoft.Azure.Search.PatternReplaceCharFilter", value = PatternReplaceCharFilter.class)
})

@bradrich-msft  Could you clarify if the CharFilter and other similar abstract class accept customer defined models?

